# Architecture — Clean Core

## Layer Isolation

The `core` layer (entities, use cases, domain logic) is **fully isolated**:

- No imports from external libraries (ORMs, HTTP frameworks, cloud SDKs).
- No direct database access. Depend on **interfaces** (ports), not implementations.
- Framework-specific code lives in `infra` or `adapters` layers only.

```
src/
  core/           # Entities, Use Cases, Domain Services — zero external deps
    entities/
    use-cases/
    ports/        # Interfaces (repositories, gateways)
  infra/          # Implementations of ports (DB, HTTP clients, queues)
    repositories/
    services/
  adapters/       # Controllers, presenters, route handlers
    http/
    cli/
```

## Dependency Inversion

- Use cases receive dependencies via constructor injection (ports/interfaces).
- This enables easy mocking in unit tests — no need for database or network in core tests.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — use case depends directly on ORM
import { db } from '../infra/database';

export class CreateTenant {
  async execute(data: CreateTenantDTO) {
    return db.insert(tenants).values(data);
  }
}

// ✅ GOOD — depends on interface, injected via constructor
export class CreateTenant {
  constructor(private readonly tenantRepo: TenantRepository) {}

  async execute(data: CreateTenantDTO) {
    return this.tenantRepo.create(data);
  }
}
```

## Testing Strategy

- **Unit tests** for `core` — fast, no I/O, mock all ports.
- **Integration tests** for `infra` — real DB (use testcontainers or in-memory).
- **E2E tests** for critical flows — full stack with HTTP requests.
